<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 08 at 12:47PM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHWESTERN PITTSBURG COUNTY
THROUGH 115 PM CDT...
At 1246 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 4 miles
west of Haywood, moving southeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Mcalester...                      Kiowa...
Savanna...                        Haywood...
Blanco...                         Pittsburg...
Arpelar...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
